metadata.name: Gaze Of The Lost Traveler
metadata.description:
I never thought you would turn out to be like this.
Kicking up the dust off your shoes.
You went far away.
But today when the winds of time finally bring fog, mist and smoke.
You came back and gave me the gaze of the lost traveler.
You never wanted to give away your freedom.
But I never wanted your freedom.

I just wanted us to become fantasy.
I just wanted us to become one all together.
